Sentencas: A new type of material, Ni1-xCoxO, was developed for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathode/interconnect contact applications.
Titulo: Development of Ni1-xCoxO as the cathode/interconnect contact for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The phase structure, coefficient of thermal expansion, sintering behavior, electrical properties, and mechanical bonding strength of these materials were evaluated against the requirements of the SOFC cathode/interconnect contact.
Titulo: Development of Ni1-xCoxO as the cathode/interconnect contact for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A dense cathode/interconnect contact layer was developed through reaction sintering from Ni and Co metal powders.
Titulo: Development of Ni1-xCoxO as the cathode/interconnect contact for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An area specific resistance (ASR) as low as 5.5 m Omega cm(2) was observed after 1200 h exposure in air at 800 degrees C for the LSM/Ni0.33Co0.67O/AISI441 assembly.
Titulo: Development of Ni1-xCoxO as the cathode/interconnect contact for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Average mechanical strengths of 6.8 and 5.0 MPa were obtained for the cathode/contact/cathode and interconnect/contact/interconnect structures, respectively.
Titulo: Development of Ni1-xCoxO as the cathode/interconnect contact for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The significantly low ASR was probably due to the dense structure and therefore improved electrical conductivity of the Ni0.33Co0.67O contact and the good bonding of the interfaces between the contact and the cathode, and between the contact and the interconnect.
Titulo: Development of Ni1-xCoxO as the cathode/interconnect contact for solid oxide fuel cells
